You're wrong. You're wrong.
You give her what she wants.

01:18:53.522 --> 01:18:56.272
Convince her you're in love with her.
Tell her that you're leaving me.

01:18:56.441 --> 01:18:57.821
- I'm not gonna do that.
- Yes.

01:18:57.984 --> 01:19:00.404
She is in love with you.
If you make her believe...

01:19:00.570 --> 01:19:02.700
...that you feel the same way,
she will stay with you.

01:19:02.864 --> 01:19:04.914
She will have the baby for you.

01:19:05.075 --> 01:19:06.535
- Laura's right.
- No, she isn't.

01:19:06.701 --> 01:19:10.041
In her mind, I am keeping
the two of you apart.

01:19:10.205 --> 01:19:11.915
You convince her that you love her.

01:19:13.208 --> 01:19:15.288
When you meet her,
you have to make her believe you.

01:19:15.460 --> 01:19:18.340
That you want to have the baby
with her and not with me.

01:19:25.720 --> 01:19:28.970
I don't wanna know what you have to do.
I don't ever...

01:19:29.141 --> 01:19:30.431
...need to hear about it.

01:19:30.600 --> 01:19:36.310
But you do whatever it takes
to bring my baby back.

01:19:51.413 --> 01:19:54.293
You should take her to the lake house.

01:19:54.749 --> 01:19:58.419
Tell her that you're thinking
of moving there.

01:19:58.753 --> 01:20:00.553
With her.

01:20:32.454 --> 01:20:34.504
Stay with me.

01:20:40.170 --> 01:20:42.960
The new exhibit's right that way.

01:21:44.192 --> 01:21:46.192
Wait, Anna.

01:21:46.820 --> 01:21:48.280
Anna.

01:22:45.795 --> 01:22:47.505
Oh, my God.

01:22:47.672 --> 01:22:49.052
I love it.

01:22:54.971 --> 01:22:56.891
It's so beautiful.

01:22:57.098 --> 01:23:00.018
Yeah, it was my father's. Laura hates it.

01:23:02.479 --> 01:23:04.519
I guess I should've sold it...

01:23:04.689 --> 01:23:06.569
...but part of me
always wanted to live here.

01:23:27.504 --> 01:23:31.014
God, I love it so much, John.

01:23:32.801 --> 01:23:34.511
Can we live here?

01:23:34.678 --> 01:23:36.468
Just us?

01:23:36.638 --> 01:23:38.428
Yes.

01:23:38.640 --> 01:23:41.060
After I file those divorce papers.

01:23:41.226 --> 01:23:43.226
Just us.

01:23:50.318 --> 01:23:54.858
I'm gonna make you so happy, John.

01:23:55.824 --> 01:23:58.244
I want you to know...

01:23:59.160 --> 01:24:02.580
...everything that I am...

01:24:03.707 --> 01:24:05.827
...is yours.

01:24:11.631 --> 01:24:13.801
All of me...

01:24:14.467 --> 01:24:16.637
...everything...

01:24:18.054 --> 01:24:20.144
...forever.

01:25:14.569 --> 01:25:16.359
Laura?

01:25:21.159 --> 01:25:22.989
Laura?

01:25:52.106 --> 01:25:54.186
I couldn't sleep.

01:26:03.660 --> 01:26:05.410
It's beautiful.

01:26:06.621 --> 01:26:08.211
A leap of faith.

01:26:24.639 --> 01:26:26.389
Yeah.

01:26:28.643 --> 01:26:31.983
I can't stay long,
because I told her that...

01:26:32.146 --> 01:26:33.516
Yeah.

01:26:33.690 --> 01:26:36.150
I told her I had to pick up some papers.

01:26:37.652 --> 01:26:39.742
Okay.

01:26:43.199 --> 01:26:45.409
Laura, I...

01:26:45.577 --> 01:26:47.157
- It's okay.
- No. I...

01:26:47.996 --> 01:26:50.666
- ...just...
- It's okay.

01:26:51.207 --> 01:26:53.077
Come here.

01:28:07.075 --> 01:28:08.985
She's gonna stay
at the lake house tonight.

01:28:11.162 --> 01:28:14.122
She agreed to go to
the doctor's with me tomorrow.

01:28:20.338 --> 01:28:22.838
It's happening. Contractions.

01:28:23.007 --> 01:28:26.177
I'm okay. I'm going to St. Agnes Hospital.

01:28:26.344 --> 01:28:27.894
Come as soon as you can.

01:28:28.054 --> 01:28:29.474
It's our baby.

01:28:29.639 --> 01:28:30.969
- I have to go there.
- No. No, no.

01:28:31.140 --> 01:28:32.730
- She cannot see you.
- John.

01:28:32.892 --> 01:28:35.102
I know, just trust me. Okay?

01:28:35.269 --> 01:28:37.649
Please, just trust me.

01:28:46.698 --> 01:28:49.198
Excuse me.
I'm looking for a patient. Anna Walsh.

01:28:49.367 --> 01:28:52.907
- Are you a relative? Okay.
- She's having my son, yes.

01:28:53.121 --> 01:28:55.161
- I got here as soon as I could.
- Thanks for coming.

01:28:55.373 --> 01:28:58.173
No, I'm sorry. I don't have a patient
listed under the last name Walsh.

01:28:58.334 --> 01:29:00.424
Try Taylor. My last name is Taylor.

01:29:02.755 --> 01:29:04.665
- No. No Taylors.
- That's... That's impossible.

01:29:04.841 --> 01:29:06.761
No, there has to be a Taylor
or a Walsh in there.

01:29:06.926 --> 01:29:08.586
- No, I have neither.
- She's not here, John.

01:29:08.761 --> 01:29:10.811
She never checked in.

01:29:11.681 --> 01:29:13.311
Where the hell could she be?

01:30:04.901 --> 01:30:07.031
Miss Havisham?

01:30:09.322 --> 01:30:11.952
Miss Havisham, where are you?

01:30:16.871 --> 01:30:19.421
Miss Havisham...

01:30:22.001 --> 01:30:25.051
Are you hiding in the pantry?

01:31:34.365 --> 01:31:36.445
What the hell is that smell?

01:32:19.035 --> 01:32:22.365
Oh, my God. Oh, my God.

01:32:24.957 --> 01:32:26.957
Oh, my God.

01:32:57.490 --> 01:32:58.570
Oh, Jesus.

01:33:26.435 --> 01:33:29.555
Hi, this is Laura Taylor.
Leave a message...

01:33:46.122 --> 01:33:47.122
Oh, God.

01:33:55.548 --> 01:33:56.838
Okay. Okay.

01:33:59.176 --> 01:34:00.586
911, what's your emergency?

01:34:00.761 --> 01:34:03.431
Please, come now. She's having the baby.

01:34:03.597 --> 01:34:04.597
No!

01:34:05.516 --> 01:34:06.636
No, no!

01:34:22.325 --> 01:34:25.075
She's dropping.
Let's get those fluids going.

01:34:25.786 --> 01:34:28.326
Laura. Laura, can you hear me?

01:34:28.497 --> 01:34:29.617
She's unresponsive.

01:34:29.790 --> 01:34:30.830
- Wide open.
- Okay.

01:34:31.000 --> 01:34:33.420
We got a female, early 40s.
Possible head trauma.

01:34:33.586 --> 01:34:36.666
Pressure 85/55 and dropping.

01:34:36.839 --> 01:34:38.839
All right, let's cross-type and match.

01:34:39.008 --> 01:34:40.468
Make sure the CAT scan...

01:35:40.528 --> 01:35:43.658
Hey. Can you hear me?

01:35:45.032 --> 01:35:46.782
John?

01:35:47.910 --> 01:35:49.910
You're gonna be fine.

01:35:50.121 --> 01:35:52.831
Doctor says you just have
a bad concussion, some stitches...

01:35:52.998 --> 01:35:55.418
...but you're gonna be okay.

01:35:55.584 --> 01:35:56.794
Where's my baby?

01:35:57.878 --> 01:35:59.838
We can't find Anna.

01:36:03.926 --> 01:36:05.586
It's Roland. Yeah.

01:36:05.761 --> 01:36:07.931
I'm across the river
at Montgomery Hospital.

01:36:08.097 --> 01:36:11.097
Anna walked into ER in labour
after she attacked Laura.

01:36:11.308 --> 01:36:14.978
Gave birth to a healthy baby boy,
according to her records.

01:36:15.521 --> 01:36:17.691
She left later that evening
and took the baby with her.

01:36:17.982 --> 01:36:20.152
- Where did she go?
- She disappeared.

01:36:20.317 --> 01:36:22.027
I told the police to put an APB...

01:36:22.236 --> 01:36:24.406
...out on her in every city
she's ever lived in...

01:36:24.572 --> 01:36:28.122
...including that military base in
Pensacola where Mike was stationed.

01:36:28.325 --> 01:36:30.735
John, she has that baby...

01:36:30.911 --> 01:36:32.661
...she's gonna wanna be someplace safe.

01:36:32.872 --> 01:36:35.082
- And close by.
- All right, thanks.

01:36:37.334 --> 01:36:41.424
The lake house.
It's gotta be the lake house.

01:36:42.465 --> 01:36:44.715
- No, babe. What are you doing?
- John.

01:36:45.009 --> 01:36:46.929
- Please, I have to go.
- I can't let you do that.

01:36:47.094 --> 01:36:50.564
John, I am going to get my child back.

01:36:59.273 --> 01:37:00.273
No. No, no, no.

01:37:00.441 --> 01:37:02.531
I let you come with me,
but this is as far as you go.

01:37:02.693 --> 01:37:04.653
Look, we know that she's dangerous.

01:37:05.070 --> 01:37:07.110
Just wait in the car.

01:39:16.035 --> 01:39:17.285
Hey.

01:39:24.209 --> 01:39:25.709
Shit.

01:40:32.528 --> 01:40:34.858
Oh, God! What happened?

01:40:36.365 --> 01:40:38.195
I got you. Just get in the car.

01:40:38.367 --> 01:40:40.787
- I got it.
- Come on. We gotta move.

01:40:50.295 --> 01:40:52.045
We better hurry up.

01:41:23.162 --> 01:41:24.662
Oh, shit.

01:41:26.540 --> 01:41:27.540
Cover the baby!

01:41:39.219 --> 01:41:42.509
I am sick of you, you crazy bitch.

01:43:06.557 --> 01:43:08.597
It's gonna be okay.

